[The southern hemisphere influenza epidemic is now in full swing, although relatively constrained in Oceania. No antigenically novel strains have made their appearance, and the current vaccines remain well matched. Surprisingly, RSV (respiratory syncytial virus) ranks alongside influenza as a major cause of respiratory disease to an increasingly large extent in parts of South America. - Mod.CP

